# Beta: Get information of a batch of documents


Gives various information that would help in debugging related to a batch of documents. Currently in beta, might undergo breaking changes without prior notice.

Tip: Refer to the [Troubleshooting tutorial](https://developers.glean.com/docs/indexing_api/indexing_api_troubleshooting/) for more information.



## Code Samples

### Python (API Client)

```python
from glean.api_client import Glean
import os


with Glean(
    api_token=os.getenv("GLEAN_API_TOKEN", ""),
    instance=os.getenv("GLEAN_INSTANCE", ""),
) as glean:

    res = glean.indexing.documents.debug_many(datasource="<value>", debug_documents=[])

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

### Typescript (API Client)

```typescript
import { Glean } from "@gleanwork/api-client";

const glean = new Glean({
  apiToken: process.env["GLEAN_API_TOKEN"] ?? "",
  instance: process.env["GLEAN_INSTANCE"] ?? "",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await glean.indexing.documents.debugMany({
    debugDocuments: [
      {
        objectType: "Article",
        docId: "art123",
      },
    ],
  }, "<value>");

  // Handle the result
  console.log(result);
}

run();
```

### Java (API Client)

```java
package hello.world;

import java.lang.Exception;
import java.util.List;
import org.openapis.openapi.Glean;
import org.openapis.openapi.models.components.DebugDocumentsRequest;
import org.openapis.openapi.models.operations.PostApiIndexV1DebugDatasourceDocumentsResponse;

public class Application {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        Glean sdk = Glean.builder()
                .apiToken("<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>")
                .instance("<YOUR_GLEAN_INSTANCE_HERE>")
            .build();

        PostApiIndexV1DebugDatasourceDocumentsResponse res = sdk.indexing().documents().debugMany()
                .datasource("<value>")
                .debugDocumentsRequest(DebugDocumentsRequest.builder()
                    .debugDocuments(List.of())
                    .build())
                .call();

        if (res.debugDocumentsResponse().isPresent()) {
            // handle response
        }
    }
}
```

### Go (API Client)

```go
package main

import(
	"context"
	"os"
	apiclientgo "github.com/gleanwork/api-client-go"
	"github.com/gleanwork/api-client-go/models/components"
	"log"
)

func main() {
    ctx := context.Background()

    s := apiclientgo.New(
        apiclientgo.WithSecurity(os.Getenv("GLEAN_API_TOKEN")),
        apiclientgo.WithInstance(os.Getenv("GLEAN_INSTANCE")),
    )

    res, err := s.Indexing.Documents.DebugMany(ctx, "<value>", components.DebugDocumentsRequest{
        DebugDocuments: []components.DebugDocumentRequest{},
    })
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatal(err)
    }
    if res.DebugDocumentsResponse != nil {
        // handle response
    }
}
```
